'''Irreligion in North Korea''' is difficult to measure in the country as the country is officially designated as an [[atheist state]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=bR0hIC0Xhb0C&pg=PA799&lpg=PA799&dq=Irreligion+in+North+Korea&source=bl&ots=XwO0xxwDWN&sig=XWcgWJtaHDZlJUXV7WqHNKTbf44&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CEoQ6AEwB2oVChMI8eCcpOv-xwIVw6QeCh0ozQP7#v=onepage&q=Irreligion%20in%20North%20Korea&f=false|title=Countries and Territories of the World|publisher=|accessdate=24 September 2015}}</ref> The [[North Korea]]n state persecutes those who stray from the official state-sponsored atheism and the [[North Korean cult of personality|personality cult]] promoted by the [[Juche idea|''Juche'' idea]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://religion.blogs.cnn.com/2011/12/20/my-take-kim-jong-il-and-the-danger-of-deifying-leaders/|title=My Take: Kim Jong Il and the danger of deifying leaders|publisher=|accessdate=24 September 2015}}</ref> North Koreans, by Western definitions, would be considered [[non-religious]] but [[Buddhism|Buddhist]] and [[Confucianism|Confucian]] traditions still play a part in North Korean life.{{refn|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=jbIVAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA506&lpg=PA506&dq=atheism+in+North+Korea&source=bl&ots=KXsSf0OF3Y&sig=l4Lf0udKJAofUhAETk2z_UNHcUY&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CB8Q6AEwADgUahUKEwj-mtfX8f7HAhUBpR4KHdyECes#v=onepage&q=atheism%20in%20North%20Korea&f=false|title=The Oxford Handbook of Atheism|publisher=|accessdate=24 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nation.com.pk/blogs/09-Feb-2015/a-tale-of-two-absurdities-the-ridiculous-policies-of-north-korea-and-turkmenistan|title=A tale of two absurdities: the ridiculous policies of North Korea and Turkmenistan|date=9 February 2015|work=The Nation|accessdate=24 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.discovermagazine.com/gnxp/2012/12/conservative-atheists-not-rare-in-south-korea/#.VfsfyNJVhBc|title=Conservative atheists not rare in South Korea?|work=Gene Expression|accessdate=24 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.charismamag.com/blogs/272-j15/features/atheism---north-korea/799-inside-the-dungeon-of-atheism|title=Inside the Dungeon of Atheism|author=Alex  Buchan|work=Charisma Magazine|accessdate=24 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.economist.com/blogs/erasmus/2015/08/varieties-atheism|title=Varieties of atheism|work=The Economist|accessdate=24 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.telegraph.co.uk/news/tomchiversscience/100125016/kim-jong-il-was-a-lefty-atheist-in-the-same-way-that-hitler-was-a-conservative-catholic/|title=Kim Jong-il was a Lefty atheist in the same way that Hitler was a conservative Catholic|work=News - Telegraph Blogs|accessdate=24 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nknews.org/2013/09/from-kim-to-christ-how-religion-works-for-north-koreans/|title=From Kim to Christ: Why religion works for North Koreans|publisher=|accessdate=24 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=TA3k123JEkEC&pg=PT99&lpg=PT99&dq=atheism+in+North+Korea&source=bl&ots=XDJJr17ni4&sig=Kd6eeeezfXs-EprV7BaGQ37NzVE&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CEkQ6AEwCDgUahUKEwj-mtfX8f7HAhUBpR4KHdyECes#v=onepage&q=atheism%20in%20North%20Korea&f=false|title=Mere Atheism|publisher=|accessdate=24 September 2015}}</ref>}}{{Excessive citations inline |date=July 2017}}

